Currently, the Installation Wizard starts with the license page, followed by database configuration.
It would be better to start with database setup, follwed by restore. Only if no valid license data can be found in either the database or the backup file, the licence page should be displayed.

Reason: in a desaster recovery scenario, the valid license data is present in the database and/or the backup file. Insisting on entering a (temporary) license (that will be overwritten soon after) slows down the installation.

