Users want more flexibility in how they access JIRA data from Confluence. The \{jiraissues\} macro is great for viewing an issue list, but it can't be used as input to other macros like \{chart\}. I know \{gadget\} can display JIRA charts, but a user came up with an interesting scenario that can't currently be achieved.

- Data resides in 2 systems: test results in a SQL db, and issues in JIRA
- The user wants to combine queries from both systems in a single chart

I could see this working in this way:

\{chart\}
  \{csv:url=JIRA CVS URL\}
  \{sql\}SELECT...\{sql\}
\{chart\}

But the csv URL is not retrieved as the user viewing the page, which is why the trusted connection needs to be used. We don't want to allow SQL access to JIRA because it circumvents security restrictions. We also won't allow the use of user credentials in the JIRA URL, for obvious reasons.

I have tried:
\{chart\}
  \{jiraissues:renderMode=static\}
\{chart\}

but the chart macro doesn't seem to be able to interpret the data returned by jiraissues.

